   966Рєњ## Bits and pieces Рђд
   968Рєњ### .parse() and .parseAsync()
   970РєњCall with no parameters to parse `process.argv`. Detects Electron and special node options like `node --eval`. Easy mode!
   971Рєњ
   972РєњOr, call with an array of strings to parse, and optionally where the user arguments start by specifying where the arguments are `from`:
   973Рєњ
   974Рєњ- `'node'`: default, `argv[0]` is the application and `argv[1]` is the script being run, with user arguments after that
   975Рєњ- `'electron'`: `argv[0]` is the application and `argv[1]` varies depending on whether the electron application is packaged
   976Рєњ- `'user'`: just user arguments
   977Рєњ
   978РєњFor example:
   979Рєњ
